Task 1:
///Lab: Basic SSRF against the local server///

Visit the site in burpsuite's browser and check one of the products stock. Then visit http history. You will see a POST /product/stock request. Send it to repeater.
At the end of the request there is a line: 
stockApi=http%3A%2F%2Fstock.weliketoshop.net%3A8080%2Fproduct%2Fstock%2Fcheck%3FproductId%3D1%26storeId%3D1
This is the line where the browser asks down the servers data, what if we change this? Usually behind every site there is an admin api, The lab gives us this: "http://localhost/admin"
So copy this address into the request like: 
stockApi=http://localhost/admin
As you can see this opened the admins panel, where we can delete 2 users profile: wiener and carlos. For solve the lab we must delete carlos's profile...:
in the source code the delete part is looks like this:
                       <div>
                            <span>carlos - </span>
                            <a href="/admin/delete?username=carlos">Delete</a>
                        </div>
So all we have to do is copy this into our stockapi part like: 
stockApi=http://localhost/admin/delete?username=carlos and send it.

